<h2 class="section-title">The Benefits of Managed WordPress Hosting</h2>
<div class="section-content"><p>The best WordPress hosting starts with a hosting provider that knows WordPress. Sure, you could always host your website or blog with just about anyone that has a server connected to the internet, but that also means entrusting your website to those that may not have the proper setup in place to ensure continued uptime and stability. Even worse, if you try to go it alone you could end up in over your head at precisely the time that your WordPress site matters most.</p>
<p>That's why many brands, companies and organizations choose managed WordPress hosting. From blazing-fast performance and all the security you'll need to prevent rogue actors from getting into your site and data, the right WordPress hosting makes all the difference. It's important, too, because WordPress is so powerful. In fact, over 40 percent of the web is built on WordPress, meaning that WordPress can change and adapt to your needs, even if you have much larger plans than where your website sits today.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Cheap and Fast WordPress Hosting</strong></h2>
<p>WordPress is one of the most extensible and widely used platforms on the web, and you need a WordPress hosting partner that knows what they're doing. Forget about trying to troubleshoot issues at 2 a.m. and hoping you get it all worked out by the time business opens tomorrow. Our WordPress plans are designed to meet the needs and demands of your website so that you can focus more on growing your audience and your business.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We're also one of the cheapest WordPress hosting solutions out there, but that doesn't mean we offer a cheap service. We provide a comprehensive WordPress hosting solution, all backed by our 24/7/365 Guru Crew. That can help make hosting on WordPress easy, and you'll also benefit from our servers that are designed to optimize the WordPress experience for both those working on your WordPress site and those using it. We'll even throw in a free Let's Encrypt SSL certificate so that you can offer the same great and secure service that people depend on.</p>
<p>Get started today by comparing plans or contact us to discuss your needs.</p></div>
